{"id": "EUVD-2024-51823", "enisaUuid": "bec91ba2-43f4-3814-8425-3d026c3d1147", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nsvcrdma: Address an integer overflow\n\nDan Carpenter reports:\n> Commit 78147ca8b4a9 (\"svcrdma: Add a \"parsed chunk list\" data\n> structure\") from Jun 22, 2020 (linux-next), leads to the following\n> Smatch static checker warning:\n>\n>\tnet/sunrpc/xprtrdma/svc_rdma_recvfrom.c:498 xdr_check_write_chunk()\n>\twarn: potential user controlled sizeof overflow 'segcount * 4 * 4'\n>\n> net/sunrpc/xprtrdma/svc_rdma_recvfrom.c\n>     488 static bool xdr_check_write_chunk(struct svc_rdma_recv_ctxt *rctxt)\n>     489 {\n>     490         u32 segcount;\n>     491         __be32 *p;\n>     492\n>     493         if (xdr_stream_decode_u32(&rctxt->rc_stream, &segcount))\n>                                                               ^^^^^^^^\n>\n>     494                 return false;\n>     495\n>     496         /* A bogus segcount causes this buffer overflow check to fail. */\n>     497         p = xdr_inline_decode(&rctxt->rc_stream,\n> --> 498                               segcount * rpcrdma_segment_maxsz * sizeof(*p));\n>\n>\n> segcount is an untrusted u32.  On 32bit systems anything >= SIZE_MAX / 16 will\n> have an integer overflow and some those values will be accepted by\n> xdr_inline_decode().", "datePublished": "2024-12-24T12:30:43", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T21:31:45", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/21e1cf688fb0397788c8dd42e1e0b08d58ac5c7b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c1f8195bf68edd2cef0f18a4cead394075a54b5a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/838dd342962cef4c320632a5af48d3c31f2f9877", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4cbc3ba6dc2f746497cade60bcbaa82ae3696689", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e5c440c227ecdc721f2da0dd88b6358afd1031a7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3c63d8946e578663b868cb9912dac616ea68bfd0", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53151", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00001.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53151"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "02f0e347-ac16-387c-bf39-77f4bec0f320", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "78147ca8b4a9b6cf0e597ddd6bf17959e08376c2 <c1f8195bf68edd2cef0f18a4cead394075a54b5a"}, {"id": "05985cc9-1581-3ae0-8f41-463dc0ab33d2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.11"}, {"id": "1ce2b798-2889-3070-a11e-3d9dc8db898c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "29e6acf4-30d1-33ea-bdc5-f8fbdddaa23f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "78147ca8b4a9b6cf0e597ddd6bf17959e08376c2 <e5c440c227ecdc721f2da0dd88b6358afd1031a7"}, {"id": "3aebfca6-ac9c-31b4-8075-fbb85a723b6f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "78147ca8b4a9b6cf0e597ddd6bf17959e08376c2 <3c63d8946e578663b868cb9912dac616ea68bfd0"}, {"id": "3d26ba6a-b9aa-3f43-a3cb-d49159b29095", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.174"}, {"id": "48dfd11b-da79-3017-b918-b4d530a024ec", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "78147ca8b4a9b6cf0e597ddd6bf17959e08376c2 <838dd342962cef4c320632a5af48d3c31f2f9877"}, {"id": "53e55748-b23f-3f54-969d-145b3d19b5ea", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "78147ca8b4a9b6cf0e597ddd6bf17959e08376c2 <4cbc3ba6dc2f746497cade60bcbaa82ae3696689"}, {"id": "9cdf92ec-3ae6-3b0f-a753-a8ec35d7eb10", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.64"}, {"id": "a2572ba3-fbbc-3c59-bce6-6b6707fe4331", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.2"}, {"id": "b807c51b-d521-35d8-9f7b-ef23c9fa59db", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.11.11"}, {"id": "eb9830ed-e4e0-3f61-8678-ecd910808865", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.120"}, {"id": "ec58dd7f-4112-36e1-8eef-94f01c80fc1e",